Hmm. Consider:

    &lt;http://example.org/countries/Canada&gt;

vs.

    &lt;http://www.example.org/countries/Canada&gt;

Syntactically different authorities (even though &quot;really&quot; the same
authority), but probably the same resource...

Justin


